 compiles and uses `aload_0; ldc; invokevirtual java/lang/ClassLoader.getResources`. It does, which is a positive sign! The instrumentation seems to cover the call site before dispatch as well, which is reassuring. This indicates that everything is working as intended so far, and I can move forward with confidence in how these extensions are being utilized in the context of resource handling.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test suite options**\\n\\nIt looks like the test suite still has our new addition, but I’m wondering if the harness expects at least one test to run. It might be wise to check if AGENTS advises against running tests. Maybe I should add a file and leave a placeholder? The final step could mention not to run it. I'll need to use the write function for that. Let's clarify how to proceed!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FwDz8dMSclt5W4pTuxSD7Rjd|fc_03b7cd5c8bd989c40169f8db3ff65081949a3cf9ac723ea27b", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.squareup.okio/okio-jvm/3.0.0/src/test/kotlin/com_squareup_okio/okio_jvm/ResourceFileSystemInnerCompanionTest.kt", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_squareup_okio.okio_jvm\n\nimport okio.Path.Companion.toPath\nimport okio.asResourceFileSystem\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport java.net.URL\nimport java.util.Collections\nimport java.util.Enumeration\n\npublic class ResourceFileSystemInnerCompanionTest {\n    @Test\n    fun asResourceFileSystemQueriesClasspathRootResources(): Unit {\n        val classLoader: RecordingResourceClassLoader = RecordingResourceClassLoader()\n        val resourceFileSystem = classLoader.asResourceFileSystem()\n\n        assertThat(resourceFileSystem.metadataOrNull(\"/anything.txt\".toPath())).isNull()\n        assertThat(classLoader.requestedResourceNames)\n            .containsExactly(\"\", \"META-INF/MANIFEST.MF\")\n    }\n\n    private class RecordingResourceClassLoader : ClassLoader(null) {\n        val requestedResourceNames: MutableList<String> = mutableListOf()\n\n        override fun getResources(name: String): Enumeration<URL> {\n            requestedResourceNames += name\n            return Collections.emptyEnumeration()\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 657, "output": 1655, "cacheRead": 16384, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18696, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777916717478, "responseId": "resp_03b7cd5c8bd989c40169f8db2ded6481948d067cf0f8da950e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_FwDz8dMSclt5W4pTuxSD7Rjd|fc_03b7cd5c8bd989c40169f8db3ff65081949a3cf9ac723ea27b", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1286 bytes to tests/src/com.squareup.okio/okio-jvm/3.0.0/src/test/kotlin/com_squareup_okio/okio_jvm/ResourceFileSystemInnerCompanionTest.kt"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777916740729}]}
